{"key":"processedPost-13335093","value":{"id":13335093,"first":13321364,"last":13343313,"when":1287071912,"utime":"10/14/10 06:58 PM","content":"It's not wise to invent your own methods on your first few grows.&nbsp; When spawning to bulk, you don't put the trays in a terrarium or mist them until fully colonized.&nbsp; You're supposed to cover the trays with foil for two weeks to fully colonize.&nbsp; At that time, you unwrap them and place in the terrarium.<br /><br />Furthermore, when a bulk substrate such as coir contaminates, it means your original spawn was contaminated.&nbsp; Mold spores won't germinate on properly pasteurized coir for several weeks at least.<br />RR","title":"Re: Shotgun FC Problems Casing Trays Contam?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}